# Cypress MCP

Global MCP entry in `~/.cursor/mcp.json` (same pattern as Playwright):

```json
"cypress": {
  "command": "npx",
  "args": ["-y", "@tms-cymcp/cypress-mcp@latest"]
}
```

Package: [`@tms-cymcp/cypress-mcp`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@tms-cymcp/cypress-mcp) — use the **scoped** name. The unscoped `cypress-mcp` on npm is a different package (test-runner only).

## Playwright parity

| Playwright MCP | Cypress MCP |
|----------------|-------------|
| `browser_navigate` | `browser_navigate` |
| `browser_click` | `browser_click` |
| `browser_type` | `browser_type` |
| `browser_snapshot` | `browser_snapshot` |
| `browser_take_screenshot` | `browser_screenshot` |
| `browser_tabs` | `browser_list_tabs` / `browser_switch_tab` |

Cypress MCP also adds `browser_run_cypress`, `browser_generate_test`, network mocks, storage/cookies, etc.

## Optional: default app URL

```json
"cypress": {
  "command": "npx",
  "args": [
    "-y",
    "@tms-cymcp/cypress-mcp@latest",
    "--base-url",
    "http://localhost:9000"
  ]
}
```

Or set `CYPRESS_BASE_URL` in the server `env` block.

## Optional: wire into an existing Cypress project

For running against your real `cypress.config` (not the auto temp project), add to `setupNodeEvents`:

```javascript
const { cypressMcp } = require('@tms-cymcp/cypress-mcp/plugin');
// inside setupNodeEvents:
cypressMcp(on, config);
```

And in `cypress/support/e2e.ts`:

```typescript
import '@tms-cymcp/cypress-mcp/support';
```

Then run `npx @tms-cymcp/cypress-mcp` from that project directory.

## Jenkins CI fix loop

Use `/jenkins-fix-cycle-cy` with a Jenkins `testReport/api/json` URL to fetch `.cy.ts` failures and run this fix cycle (mirror of `/jenkins-fix-cycle-pw` for Playwright).

## Test execution loop (separate package)

For “run spec → read failures → rerun” without browser tools, see [`cypress-mcp`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/cypress-mcp) (jams4code) with `--cwd /path/to/project`.
